From:Sergio H
I enjoy your posts and appreciate your opinion. I thought it was interesting to
note that the list was made up of stocks hitting or near new highs but
undervalued relative to their GN.

I really like your strategy of having stocks ready for when you want to reload
or rebalance your portfolio. Capturing undervalued GN and reviewing for
tangible book value are a good start as is setting a max for acceptable debt to
earnings ratio. I don't agree with eliminating stocks that are at or near highs
since this does not imply that the value is shrinking.

Stocks could be hitting new highs along with improving metrics similarly to
stocks hitting new lows could be experiencing a decline in value metrics. New
highs do not prevent higher highs and new lows do not indicate a bottom.
