Date:1/25/2012 2:15:39 PM
From:E_K_S
Hi Paul -

Where do you find the time series for companies with "Growing BV"? I can easily
find stated BV for companies but it is hard for me to see if BV is growing over
time w/o going through several of the old annual company reports. Do you know
of a site that shows several years of financials that also includes BV over
time?

My premise is to find those companies that have grown their BV over the last
five year. These companies should do even better in a low interest rate
environment (ie low cost of capital). Of course, I want companies that are
profitable and have been able to grow revenues, maintain and/or increase
margins but also have grown their stated BV.

I thought that starting a screen w/ companies that have grown their BV over the
last five years, I could then thin down the list w/ this other criteria to find
some good value "Buy" candidates.

