I'm never quite comfortable with metrics that use FCF. And here's an example of
it. You have a positive "13% - 14% FCF yield", and positive "FCF margins"
whereas the sites I am using show a negative FCF number (which I assume would
make yield and margins negative). I don't know whether it's definitional
differences (Yahoo says "levered" free cash flow is negative) or what, but the
dichotomy -- an apparent plus FCF metric vs. a negative FCF number that I see
-- confuses me. No matter though. It's only important that you know how your
calculations stand in context as to what a value bogey is for you. . If you say
it's a value or value possibility or takeover possibility, it very well could
be. I don't see PMC as a value for me at current price, so I'll pass.
